<div class="container warning" id="summary">
    <div class="container-header">Summary of Changes Made</div>
    <div class="container-content">
        <div class="container-content-inner">
            <h3>web-dev (Port 3000) - Development Container</h3>
            <table class="diagnostic-table">
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>File</strong></td>
                        <td>Comserv/docker-entrypoint.sh</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Change</strong></td>
                        <td>Added line 94: <code>chown -R comserv:comserv ${CATALYST_HOME}/root/log</code></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Why</strong></td>
                        <td>Fixes EACCES (permission denied) error when supervisor tries to spawn comserv-server process</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Status</strong></td>
                        <td>✅ Applied - Needs rebuild</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            
            <h3>web-prod (Port 5000) - Production Container</h3>
            <table class="diagnostic-table">
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>File</strong></td>
                        <td>Comserv/docker-compose.prod.yml</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Change</strong></td>
                        <td>Removed entire ./root bind mount; now mount only:
                            <ul>
                            <li><code>./root/static:/opt/comserv/root/static:ro</code> (read-only)</li>
                            <li><code>./root/Documentation:/opt/comserv/root/Documentation:ro</code> (read-only)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Why</strong></td>
                        <td>Fixes OCI runtime error caused by nested volume mount conflict inside read-only parent directory</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Status</strong></td>
                        <td>✅ Applied - Needs rebuild</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container" id="web_dev_rebuild">
    <div class="container-header">web-dev Container - Step-by-Step Rebuild</div>
    <div class="container-content">
        <div class="container-content-inner">
            <h3>Option 1: Using Docker Desktop GUI (Recommended for Learning)</h3>
            
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Open Docker Desktop</strong> on your machine</li>
                <li><strong>Navigate to Containers</strong> section</li>
                <li><strong>Find comserv-web-dev</strong> container
                    <ul>
                        <li>Status should show "Up" (running)</li>
                        <li>Port 3000 is currently NOT listening due to old image</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Stop the container</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Click the "Stop" button (square icon) next to comserv-web-dev</li>
                        <li>Wait for status to change to "Exited"</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Delete the old container</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Right-click on comserv-web-dev → "Delete" or click trash icon</li>
                        <li>Confirm deletion</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Delete the old image</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Go to "Images" section</li>
                        <li>Find "comserv" image (should have "dev" tags)</li>
                        <li>Click trash icon to delete</li>
                        <li>This forces Docker to rebuild from scratch with our changes</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Rebuild the image</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Open terminal/command prompt</li>
                        <li>Navigate to: <code>cd /home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2</code></li>
                        <li>Run: <code>docker-compose up -d web-dev</code></li>
                        <li>Docker will rebuild the image with the chown fix</li>
                        <li>Wait 30-60 seconds for build to complete</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Verify port 3000 is listening</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Run: <code>curl http://localhost:3000/health</code></li>
                        <li>Should return HTTP 200 response</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>
            
            <h3>Option 2: Using Command Line (Faster)</h3>
            
            <pre><code># Stop and remove old container
docker-compose down

# Remove cached image to force rebuild
docker rmi comserv-web-dev 2>/dev/null || true

# Rebuild and start with our changes
docker-compose up -d web-dev

# Wait for startup and health check
sleep 15
docker ps | grep web-dev

# Test port 3000
curl http://localhost:3000/health</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Expected Output After Rebuild</h3>
            <pre><code>$ curl http://localhost:3000/health
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
[JSON response or health indicator]

$ docker ps
CONTAINER ID   STATUS            NAMES
abc123def456   Up 2m (healthy)   comserv-web-dev

$ docker logs comserv-web-dev | grep EACCES
[No output - errors are gone]</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container" id="web_prod_rebuild">
    <div class="container-header">web-prod Container - Step-by-Step Rebuild</div>
    <div class="container-content">
        <div class="container-content-inner">
            <h3>IMPORTANT: Check Environment Variables First</h3>
            
            <p>web-prod requires environment variables to be set. Before rebuilding, verify these are configured:</p>
            
            <pre><code>COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_SERVER_HOST=192.168.1.198
COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_SERVER_PORT=3306
COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_SERVER_USERNAME=shanta_forager
COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_SERVER_PASSWORD=[your_password]
COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_SERVER_DATABASE=ency
COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_FORAGER_HOST=192.168.1.198
COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_FORAGER_PORT=3306
COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_FORAGER_USERNAME=shanta_forager
COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_FORAGER_PASSWORD=[your_password]
COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_FORAGER_DATABASE=shanta_forager</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Option 1: Using Docker Desktop GUI</h3>
            
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Open Docker Desktop</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Go to Containers section</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Find comserv-web-prod</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Status should show "Created" (not running) from previous failed build</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Delete the failed container</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Right-click → "Delete" or click trash icon</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Go to Images section</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Delete the old image</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Forces rebuild from scratch</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Rebuild using command line</strong> (see Option 2 below)</li>
            </ol>
            
            <h3>Option 2: Using Command Line (Recommended)</h3>
            
            <pre><code># Navigate to Comserv directory
cd /home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2/Comserv

# Build the image (uses docker-compose.prod.yml)
docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml build

# Wait for build to complete...

# Start the container
docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d web-prod

# Wait 30-60 seconds for startup and health checks

# Verify it's running and healthy
docker ps | grep web-prod

# Check logs for any errors
docker logs comserv-web-prod | tail -20

# Test port 5000
curl http://localhost:5000/health</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Expected Output After Rebuild</h3>
            <pre><code>$ curl http://localhost:5000/health
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
[JSON response or health indicator]

$ docker ps
CONTAINER ID   STATUS            NAMES
xyz789abc123   Up 2m (healthy)   comserv-web-prod

$ docker logs comserv-web-prod | grep "read-only"
[No output - mount errors are gone]</code></pre>
            
            <h3>If Build Still Fails</h3>
            <pre><code># Check what volumes are mounted
docker exec comserv-web-prod mount | grep comserv

# Verify specific mount points exist
docker exec comserv-web-prod ls -la /opt/comserv/root/

# Check if log directory is writable
docker exec comserv-web-prod touch /opt/comserv/root/log/test.log && echo "Writable" || echo "Read-only"</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

