<div class="container" id="troubleshooting">
    <div class="container-header">Troubleshooting Common Issues</div>
    <div class="container-content">
        <div class="container-content-inner">
            <h3>Issue: "Port 3000 is already in use"</h3>
            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Stop all containers, check for hung processes</p>
            <pre><code>docker-compose down
pkill -f "starman\|supervisor" || true
sleep 5
docker-compose up -d web-dev</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Issue: "EACCES permission denied still appears"</h3>
            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Image wasn't rebuilt with changes. Delete and rebuild:</p>
            <pre><code>docker rmi comserv-web-dev 2>/dev/null || true
docker-compose down
docker-compose build --no-cache web-dev
docker-compose up -d web-dev</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Issue: "OCI runtime error - read-only file system"</h3>
            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> web-prod not using new docker-compose.prod.yml. Rebuild:</p>
            <pre><code>cd Comserv
docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml down
docker rmi comserv-web-prod 2>/dev/null || true
docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml build --no-cache
docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d web-prod</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Issue: "Health check failing (unhealthy)"</h3>
            <p><strong>Check logs:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>docker logs comserv-web-dev 2>&1 | tail -50
# or
docker logs comserv-web-prod 2>&1 | tail -50</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Issue: "curl: (7) Failed to connect"</h3>
            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Container started but application not listening yet. Wait 30-60 seconds, then retry:</p>
            <pre><code>sleep 30
curl http://localhost:3000/health</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

